From b914bfa25e678e6cb0997bb981c64be78b488005 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Wed, 22 Jul 2026 01:02:35 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add DXR hardware ray tracing (foundation + shadows)

Add a hardware DirectX Raytracing path alongside the existing rasterizer.
Milestone 1: primary rays through the camera + hard directional shadows on
the existing glTF model, toggled at runtime (F6 / ImGui checkbox).

RHI:
- Device: expose ID3D12Device5 and a RaytracingTier support check.
- CommandContext: expose ID3D12GraphicsCommandList4.
- RaytracingAccel: BLAS/TLAS builder helpers.
- RaytracingPipeline: DXR state object + global/local root signatures.

Graphics:
- RaytracingRenderer: collects scene geometry, builds acceleration
  structures + shader binding table, dispatches rays into a UAV image and
  copies it to the back buffer.
- ShaderManager: add CompileLibrary() for lib_6_3 DXR shaders.
- GltfModel / ModelRenderer: expose geometry + world matrix for BLAS.

Shader:
- HLSL/PathTrace.hlsl: raygen / miss / shadow-miss / closest-hit.

Project:
- Register new files, add d3dx12.h (DirectXTK Src) to the include path.

Runs only when the GPU/driver reports DXR support; otherwise the app
transparently keeps using the rasterizer.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01SfcRdgEzpuV52YCuhdR5ty
